'''Boris Mikhailovich Kloss''' ({{lang-rus|Борис Михайлович Клосс|p=bɐˈrʲis mʲɪˈxɐlaɪvʲɪtɕ klos}}; born 19 December 1932) is a Russian [[historian]], [[Source criticism|source critic]], specialist in [[palaeography]] and [[archeography]], a [[university professor]], Doctor of History (1989); head of the History of Religion and Church Centre, Honorary Doctor of the European University (2003), member of the International Association of the Old Slavic Studies (1992). He studied under [[Andrey Kolmogorov]], [[Lev Cherepnin]], [[Militsa Nechkina]].
[[File:The Nikon Chronicle and other Russian Chronicles of the 16-17 centuries.jpg|thumb|''The Nikon Chronicle and the Russian Chronicles of the 16th-17th centuries'', published by [[Nauka (publisher)|Nauka]] in 1980]] Kloss was born in Moscow in the family of a military man. He graduated from the Mechanics and Mathematics Faculty of the [[Moscow State University]] in 1956. In 1958 he started working for the USSR Institute of Automatics. Since 1971 he worked at the USSR Institute of History under the Russian Academy of Sciences. He completed the [[thesis]] in the topic ''The [[Nikon Chronicle]] and the Russian Chronicles of the 16th-17th centuries''.<ref>http://iriran.ru/?q=kloss</ref> In 1980-1990 he simultaneously taught at the Moscow State University, the [[Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology]] and [[Russian State University for the Humanities]]. He became a renown specialist in [[Kievan Rus']] literature, specifically in Russian [[hagiography]]. He lectured in various universities of the United States, Poland, Norway, Russia.
== Publications == * ''The Nikon Chronicle and the Russian Chronicles of the 16th-17th centuries'' ({{lang-ru|Никоновский свод и русские летописи XVI-XVII веков}}), 1980 * ''Life of St. Sergius of Radonezh'' ({{lang-ru|Житие Сергия Радонежского: Рукописная традиция}}), 1998 * ''On the Russian Hagiography of the 14th-16th centuries'' ({{lang-ru|Очерки по истории русской агиографии XIV–XVI вв.}}), 2001 * ''On the Origin of the name of Russia'' ({{lang-ru|О происхождении названия «Россия»}}), 2012 * ''[[Nikolay Chernyshevsky|Chernyshevsky]] at the Head of Revolutionaries of 1861'' ({{lang-ru|Чернышевский во главе революционеров 1861 года}}), 1981<ref>{{cite web |url=http://unicat.nlb.by/opac/pls/!search.http_keyword?query%3Da001%3D%22BY-SEK-625925%22%26lst_siz%3D20 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-11-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305011743/http://unicat.nlb.by/opac/pls/%21search.http_keyword?query=a001%3D%22BY-SEK-625925%22&lst_siz=20 |archivedate=2016-03-05 |df= }}</ref> * Editor of the modern edition of the ''[[Complete Collection of Russian Chronicles]]''.
