'''Dausdava''' ({{lang-grc|Δαούσδαυα}}) was a [[Dacians|Dacian]] town in [[Moesia]] between the [[Danube]] and the [[Balkan Mountains]], in the region between Nicopolis (modern [[Nikopol, Bulgaria]]) and [[Abritus]]{{sfn|Olteanu|loc=Toponyms}} (modern [[Razgrad]]).
