'''John Lambert''' (1937-January 11, 2016)<ref>[http://catalog.loc.gov/cgi-bin/Pwebrecon.cgi?hd=1,19&Search%5FArg=John%20Lambert&Search%5FCode=NAME%40&CNT=100&type=quick&PID=C1RE-ENM10VVZEymV9IsPd21xA0b&HIST=0&SEQ=20131225084733&SID=1 Library of Congress catalogue entry for Lambert]</ref> was a naval illustrator and historian. He specialised in naval boats up to [[destroyer]] size. The information he presented and his detailed drawings of [[warship]]s and their weapons systems are referenced from official naval and shipbuilder sources.

He has written over 350 magazine articles for ''Model Boats'', ''Airfix Magazine'', ''Scale Models'', ''Model Shipwright'', ''Interavia and Marine Modelling International''.

