{{refimprove|date=June 2017}}{{About|the architects}}
The '''Stott'''s were a family of architects from [[Oldham]], [[North West England]], of [[Scottish people|Scottish]] descent who specialised in the design of [[cotton mill]]s. James Stott was the father, Joseph and his elder brother Abraham Stott had rival practices, and in later years did not communicate. Their children continue their practices.
